description:
Trade paperback collecting Batman: The Mad Monk #1-6.

The follow-up to Batman and the Monster Men (2006) is, like its predecessor, set in the first years of the Caped Crusader's crime-fighting career. When Gotham City's police force, led by a young Captain Gordon, find a series of bodies drained of blood, Batman's search for the serial killer leads to a cult led by a charismatic figure clad in a red monk's robe, who has targeted Bruce Wayne's girlfriend as his next victim. The story updates a 1939 original and captures the flavor of thirties pulp magazines. Wagner's bold, economical drawing style and dynamic layouts make it a tale worth retelling. --Flagg, Gordon
name: Batman and the Mad Monk

description: A nameless, faceless cartoonist wanders into the Dominion branch of The Great Northern Brotherhood of Canadian Cartoonists. As the narrator leads the reader through the halls of the GNBCC building, he also takes them on a tour of Canadian cartooning history, pausing to dwell on the great, the mysterious, the awful, unflinchingly describing their foibles as well as their triumphs, and reflecting on their greatness, their contributions, and their legacy. The tale is partially based in fact, and partially in fiction, as it explores the great real-life contributions of Canadian cartoonists such as Doug Wright, and also the fictional fictions of creations such as Kao-Kuk, the first Inuit to travel to the stars.
name: Great Northern Brotherhood of Canadian Cartoonists

description:
Five part mini-series of mini-comics. This is the second series (of two); the first series can be found here. Like the first, this series was packaged and available with Drake's Cakes snack cakes, this time in 1994.

This cosmically powered five part mini-series includes many heroes and villains from the Marvel Universe.

Heroes/Teams:

  • Spider-Man
  • Silver Surfer
  • Hulk
  • Wolverine
  • Gladiator
  • Starbolt
  • Ulysses
  • Hector
  • Imperial Guard
  • X-Men
  • Pantheon

Villains:

  • Galen-Kor
  • Dylon-Cir
  • Dekker
  • Tazer
  • Kona-Lor
  • Yeti
  • Skreamer

This series contains a linked story line with the following comics (spanning five major character titles):

  • Silver Surfer: Breakout
  • The Amazing Spider-Man: When Heroes Clash
  • Hulk: Pantheon Raid
  • Wolverine: The Nuke Hunters
  • X-Men: Siege and Destroy

Though the comics are small in size (3" x 5"), it is a BIG adventure cosmically spanning from Hala to Earth!
name: Spider-Man Drakes Cakes Mini Comics Series 2

Four part mini-series of mini-comics which were packaged with Drake's Cakes snack cakes in 1993. This is the first series (of two); the second series can be found here.

The mini-series was primarily focused on Spider-Man, but there were many cameo appearances from well known heroes and villains of the time!

Heroes:

  • Hulk

Villains:

This series contains a linked story line with the following comics (spanning four major character titles):

The comics are small in size (3" x 5"), but pack a big punch with an all star character cast!
